Personal Portfolio: Design & Development Showcase
A Digital Gallery of Graphic Design and Web Development
**Key Features
Skill-Centric Design: The site is architected to highlight three core pillars: Adobe Illustrator (Vector Art), Adobe Photoshop (Raster/Photo Manipulation), and Web Design (Clean Code).

High-Fidelity 3-Column Grid: A responsive gallery that utilizes CSS Grid (repeat(3, 1fr)) to showcase work with professional alignment.

Geometric Precision: Every card uses the aspect-ratio property to ensure a consistent, organized layout that mirrors the precision of vector design.

Semantic HTML5 Architecture: Built with a focus on code quality, ensuring the site is accessible and easily indexed by search engines.

**Creative Enhancements
Dynamic Visual Hierarchy:

Focus State: On hover, images drop to 0.5 opacity, allowing the background depth to show through.

Layered Gradients: A smooth linear-gradient appears over images to provide high contrast for project labels.

Interactive Typography: Project titles slide into place using CSS transform, adding a layer of "whimsical" animation to the user experience.

Performance Engineering:

Asset Optimization: Images are compressed and optimized to maintain the high quality expected in a Photoshop portfolio while ensuring fast load times.

Lazy Loading: The loading="lazy" attribute is used to prioritize the loading of the Hero section.

Advanced Form UX:

Autocomplete Integration: The contact form uses specific autocomplete attributes (e.g., name, email) to respect professional UX standards and reduce user friction.

**Development Challenges & Solutions
1. Linking the Design Language
Challenge: Initially, the CSS file connection failed because the file was named styles.css while the HTML looked for style.css.

Solution: Changed the file naming to style.css and verified the link in the <head>, restoring the visual design immediately.

2. Maintaining Image Integrity
Challenge: Displaying a mix of Photoshop compositions and Illustrator icons in a uniform grid without distorting the artwork.

Solution: Utilized object-fit: cover within the aspect-ratio containers. This ensures that every piece of art is cropped professionally rather than stretched.

3. Security-First Scripting
Challenge: Browser warnings regarding Content Security Policy (CSP) when using certain JavaScript strings.

Solution: Refactored scripts to avoid eval() and string-based timers, opting for modern arrow functions to maintain a secure, professional environment.

